4 Contributing to theCrag - 6 Geolocation

<p>Location! Location! Location!</p>

<p>Location is pretty important.</p>


<p>How to add boundaries....</p>


<p>Location is the primary way of clustering things into areas, and regions.</p>

<p>Talk about continents, countries, possibly states, then crags and any extra levels are generally based on geogrpahy. a good source of geography based clusters is weather sources like BOM, but they should only be used if there are enough crags to warrant the extra layer</p>


